<br>
1- Always wear the best gear you can. Your opponents will have spellcrafted gear and probably even Masterpieces.<br>
<br>
2- Never fight unbuffed unless absolutely necessary. Even if there not top of the line buffs anything will help. Simply put if they are buffed and you are not your chances of survival are about equal to a feminist in a WWF crowd.<br>
<br>
Always group when possible, your group teamwork determine your sucess. Do not expect much if you run around solo. <br>
<br>
Get at least 1 preferably 2 clerics that can heal (a spec of 1 in rejuv is not a healing cleric) in your group. When possible try to get good clerics. (You will know quite soon if they are good or bad)<br>
<br>
Always stick to the &quot;Driver&quot; of the group. As soon as you stop spread out a little so you don't make a giant heap of &quot;Mez Me&quot; targets.<br>
<br>
If it has Zzzz Zzzz over his head and something else has nothing on it hit the one without first.<br>
<br>
If you see a caster with white swirls around him and see in chat xxxxx Casting has gained perfect poise-&gt; you have 2 options: If you are hitting him and he's almost dead, keep at it and pray he does not get healed. If he's full run and pray that you get healed.<br>
<br>
If it has a stick and you play in alb always kill the guys with sticks first. You are lucky and do not have to deal with friars.<br>
<br>
If you see a hib with a spear try to avoid them. They hurt you bad and will outlive you unless you get assistance.<br>
<br>
If you see hibs with 2h weapons except spears just never turn your back to them and you should be fine.<br>
<br>
If you see a lute (guitar) attack whoever is holding it!<br>
<br>
Never charge unless you are sure that others will come with you or that you suprised the enemy. Doing so without those conditions will result in a nice trip to the bindstone.<br>
<br>
Against a pure tank it's best to save flury for later in the fight when he has low life, if you do it right you can kill him before he reacts and uses IP.<br>
<br>
If you see a bow melee them, most are prety weak in melee and only the hunter can prove a slight threath if you ignore him long enough. If you see a stick carier close kill whoever you think will go down first.<br>
<br>
If you see something with a robe and a schyte it's not a caster! Avoid if possible.<br>
<br>
If you see a nice patch of mushrooms stay the hell away from it they will eventually die without your assistance.<br>
<br>
If you see a kobold with a ghostly pet following it and running strait at a bunch of you eighter target him fast and kill it or get the hell away. <br>
<br>
If you are in a keep and are defending it stay the hell away from windows.<br>
<br>
Kobolds, Lurikeens and Elves are not always casters.<br>
<br>
If you keep hitting someone and his life never drops then find a better target.<br>
<br>
When a caster is casting at you and you are running to him do not stop in front of him pass through him and stick.<br>
<br>
If you have End regen availleable always sprint in a fight.<br>
<br>
If you have good determination (3+) never waste purge on a casted stun save it for melee stuns.<br>
<br>
If you can, group a friar they have good resists buffs against very common damage types.<br>
<br>
I could think of a lot more tips but everything comes with experience.<br>
<br>
Hope you enjoy the field, good luck<br>
<br>
